description:
File: rust/lichen-schc/src/fragment.rs
Lines: 220-242 (Ack::from_bytes)

Category: CORRECTNESS

The Ack::from_bytes function reads the bitmap_len from wire data, but if the actual bitmap bytes are shorter than needed, it silently treats missing bytes as zeros:
```rust
let n = data[2] as usize;
let body = &data[3..];
let mut bitmap = [false; MAX_WINDOW_SIZE];
for i in 0..n.min(MAX_WINDOW_SIZE) {
    let byte = if i / 8 < body.len() { body[i / 8] } else { 0 };
    bitmap[i] = (byte >> (7 - (i % 8))) & 1 != 0;
}
```

If an ACK claims bitmap_len=62 but only provides 2 bytes of bitmap data (16 bits), positions 16-61 are silently set to false (indicating fragments not received).

Impact: Truncated/corrupted ACKs could trigger unnecessary retransmissions (positions beyond available data appear as 'not received'), or mask actual missing fragments if the receiver sends a proper ACK but it gets truncated in transit.

Fix: Validate that data length is sufficient for claimed bitmap_len:
```rust
let required_bytes = 3 + n.div_ceil(8);
if data.len() < required_bytes {
    return Err(TooShort::new(required_bytes, data.len()).into());
}
```
